title.narrative: Management of Integrated Control of Schistosomiasis and Intestinal Helminths in Sub-Saharan Africa (ICOSA)

description.narrative: This activity (Management of Integrated Control of Schistosomiasis and Intestinal Helminths in Sub-Saharan Africa (ICOSA)) is a component of Integrated Control of Schistosomiasis and Intestinal Helminths in Sub-Saharan Africa (ICOSA) - Phase 1 & 2 reported by FCDO, with a funding type of 'Procurement of Services' and a budget of £30,424,485. This component benefits Africa, regional, and works in the following sector(s): Health policy and administrative management, Infectious disease control. , with the following implementing partners: Crown Agents Limited, Imperial College London. The start date is 01-01-2010 and the end date is 31-03-2019.
